  "packageName": "pw-utilities",
  "readme": [
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": "# pw-utilities\n\nPlaywright utilities for stabilizing elements before taking screenshots.\n\n## Installation\n\n"
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "text": "```bash\nnpm install pw-utilities\n```"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": "\n\n## API\n\n### "
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "text": "`stabilize(locator)`"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": "\n\nScrolls the element into view and waits for its position to stop changing across animation frames before taking a screenshot. Injects a temporary red outline overlay so the element is visible in the screenshot even before the stabilization loop completes.\n\n"
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "text": "```ts\nimport { stabilize } from \"pw-utilities\";\n\nconst locator = page.locator(\"#my-element\");\nawait stabilize(locator);\nawait locator.screenshot();\n```"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": "\n\n### "
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "text": "`LocatorLike`"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": "\n\nA duck-typed interface compatible with Playwright's "
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "text": "`Locator`"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": ". This library does not depend on "
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "text": "`@playwright/test`"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": " at runtime — it uses structural typing for compatibility."
    }
  ],
